rComments: tons of readings and papers and theassignments and calculations

She's great at explaining concepts. She does lots of sample problems which helped me solidify my knowledge very well! I didn't go to office hours but i expect that she'll help out a lot. I did not like chemistry until I took this course. Remember to practice practice practice! Exams are challenging, but fair. She's really cute and sweet.

Dr. Sauer is awesome.  She gives very clear and easy to understand lectures, and has just the right amount of class involvement factored in. The tests were highly reflective of the material we were taught. The OWL homework given is all the practice I needed to ace her course.   Very good one-to-one as well: genuinely cares about students.

She is a nice professor but she is will screw you so badly with marking. Even though you talk to her about it, she will deduct marks in the most ridiculous things. She may seems so friendly and "smile" all the time but she is also very harsh.

Don't get thrown off of what other people are saying here. This is the honest truth. She is terrible and she will screw you over from the beginning till the end. Do not be fooled by her smile she is evil and she will bring you down as  much as possible.

Incredible teacher. Really knows her chemistry (both org and inorg)and makes sure the content is properly received by the students. Generally very solid. Advice: rxn problems are key, so do many of them, especially the overall synthesis ones but DO NOT forget the smaller stuff like acid-base eq's, solubility determination etc

She's very enthusiastic about what she teaches! Her exams are fair if you study for them and go to her lectures. She likes to write on her lecture slides a lot so make sure you print out the notes and follow along.

Best professor in UTSC! She's smart(Post-Dr. in Yale) and excellent at teaching, IF YOU PAID ATTENTION. Her teaching pace might be a bit too fast for some of the students, but if you understand the content right in class, you don't need to practice much because she explained everything!

Amazing Prof! So helpful. She answers emails right away and holds tons of extra office hours (yes they get busy, but she gets to everyone eventually). Super enthusiastic. Tests are fair - no major surprises as long as you've done the assignments and understand them. Made orgo really interesting.
understood the examples given, did all of the homework,but was still totally thrown off by the final. Taught too fast, not enough examples.
do not like this prof. teaches the easiest stuff but her questions are very very hard. She caused me to lose all my interest in chem. very disappointed. a lot of people drop out of her course
Very nice prof!! one of best at teaching... End of the week sections wer amazing.. Got to learn a lot..
She is awesome!!!

Amazing! Super helpful, really nice and appears invested in helping you succeed. Couldn't have asked for a better experience- she got me really interested in Chemistry- I actually changed my major after having her!!
Super awesome professor! She's super accessible and easy to approach. Study hard, ask questions and you'll do well!
Effie is an amazing prof who is more than willing to help me throughout the course. She would patiently explain things in detail in an easy to understand manner.

she is such an awesome professor! I was not looking forward to organic chem but she made learning it not as bad as I thought it would be:) make sure you do her practise problems and textbook questions and you'll be fine:d

THE BEST PROF EVERRRRRR!!!!! She explains everything so clearly, and has great examples. I love how she takes up questions daily. She is very nice and extremely helpful. I had a different prof up to the midterm, which I failed, but I had her for the second half and I managed to do well in the end. Make sure you do all the assigned homework.

Such an amazing teacher! She truly cares about students and their success. Really helpful, especially if you attend her lectures and go to her office hours. I failed the midterm and hated chem before she started teaching. She really helped me understand, and made chem lectures interesting. Such a great teacher and nice person. Thanks so much!

Very nice professor. Must attend the lectures. Do all the practice assignment and know them inside out to do excellent on her exams. Also, lectures explain everythin, dont need to read the textbook! Midterms and finals are easy. She is fair!

Very nice professor, and easy midterms however her final is NOT easy. The only way to do well on her final is if you have literally gone through every single question in her assignment and textbook and understand all the little details

Shes actually a very good teacher, knowledgable in chemistry, FOR SURE, she can teach this stuff in her sleep, Tests were fair, simple, dont really need textbook, if you have her teaching. One of the best profs i ever had.

She is very kind and helpful! She answers emails the same day, and all questions posted on her discussion board. All the questions on her exams are either found in the textbook, her lecture notes or from the homework. You can either pass her midterm OR final and you pass the course.
Although she makes her classes very interesting, her exam was pretty challenging. Make sure you do every question in the book.
BEST PROF, EASY EVERYTHING FROM LECTURE NOTES, EXAM EASY, SHES VERY NICE AND CARING AND AN OVERALL GREAT PROFESSOR. EASY A

She's such a genuinely kind person who truly cares about her students. Her final was challenging but fair...make sure you study hard! Her lectures are great and lecture notes are very thorough. Overall, a great prof!
